\begin_layout Standard
The approach of this work is not fixed to seagrass.
 It is possible to manage different scenarios and different sensors.
 As a user is able to add new sensors to the simulator (s.
 UWSim Wiki), the surface can be anything.
 The Robot can dive through chemical clouds or scan temperature - there
 is no limit for these sensoric missions.
 This approach manages to log the gained data and store it in a format to
 visualize it a Geo Information System and record it for Open-EASE.
 Therefore one can run a desired mission visualize it on a map or even in
 a 3D environment.
\end_layout

